#installing apache malven on windows

1. Download Apache Maven:
Visit the official Apache Maven website (https://maven.apache.org/download.cgi) and download the latest Maven Binary ZIP archive.

2. Extract Maven Archive:
Once the download is complete, extract the contents of the Maven archive to your desired installation directory. For example, you can extract it to C:\maven.

3. Set Environment Variables:
   - Open the System Properties dialog:
      - Right-click on the "This PC" or "My Computer" icon and select "Properties".
      - Go to "Advanced system settings".
      - Click the "Environment Variables" button.
   - Edit the "Path" variable:
      - Under the "System variables" section, locate the "Path" variable and select it.
      - Click the "Edit" button.
      - Click the "New" button and add the following entry:
        ```bash
        C:\maven\bin
        ```
      - Click "OK" to save the changes.
   - Add a new "MAVEN_HOME" variable:
      - Click the "New" button under the "System variables" section.
      - Set the "Variable name" to MAVEN_HOME.
      - Set the "Variable value" to the installation directory of Maven (C:\maven).
      - Click "OK" to save the changes.

4. Verify Maven Installation:
   - Open a new command prompt to ensure the environment variable changes take effect.
   - Run the following command to verify Maven installation:
     ```bash
     mvn -version
     ```
   #you should see the version of maven you installed

